Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addAIoFiller(25.10)                                        addAIoFiller(25.10)

Name
       addAIoFiller - Adds area I/O filler cell instances

Syntax
        addAIoFiller

       [-help]

       {-cell   <fillerCellName>  |  -cellList  {<fillerCellName1><fillerCell-
       Name2><...>}}

       [-prefix <prefix>]

       [-aioRowCluster <aioRowClusterName> | -allAIORowCluster]

       [-setPreplaced]

       [-onlyESD]

       [-onlyShoulder]

       [-onlyGap]

       [-powerDomain <powerDomainName>]

       Adds area I/O filler cell instances. Use this command during  or  after
       floorplanning. You can also use the command after the placement of man-
       ually created area I/Os.

       The command,

              * By  default,  adds  area  I/O filler cells to all the area I/O
                clusters if you do not specify  the  -aioRowCluster  and  -al-
                lAIORowCluster parameters.

              * Adds filler cells in all the blank sites of the specified area
                I/O  row clusters if you do not specify the -onlyESD, -onlyGap
                and -onlyShoulder parameters.

              * Uses any LEF CLASS PAD or CLASS PAD AREAIO for adding the area
                I/O filler cells. By default the command uses  LEF  CLASS  PAD
                SPACER  to  add filler cells, and also adds filler cells using
                any LEF CLASS PAD displaying a warning in Innovus.

              * Does not allow overlapping of filler  cells  and  places  non-
                overlapping filler cells.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each addAIoFiller parameter. For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man addAIoFiller

       -aioRowCluster <aioRowClusterName>
              Specifies the area I/O row cluster name. AIO  filler  cells  are
              added only to this cluster.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -allAIORowCluster
              Adds AIOFiller cells to all the area I/O clusters.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell <fillerCellName>
              Specifies the name of the area I/O filler cell to be added.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -cellList {<fillerCellName1> <fillerCellName2> ...}
              Specifies  the  list of area I/O filler cells that fill the gaps
              in I/O row clusters. Adds the largest filler  cell  first,  fol-
              lowed by smaller filler cells.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -onlyESD
              Specifies  to  add  ESD (electrostatic discharge) cells with the
              filler cell name in the area I/O row clusters.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -onlyGap
              Specifies to add the filler cells with the filler cell  name  to
              fill all the gaps in the area I/O row clusters.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -onlyShoulder
              Specifies to add shoulder cells with the filler cell name in the
              area I/O row clusters.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -powerDomain <powerDomainName>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the power domain in which the area I/O
              filler cells are to be added.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -prefix <prefix>
              Specifies the prefix name to be appended for the added area  I/O
              filler cell instance.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -setPreplaced
              Sets the status of the area I/O filler cells as preplaced.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The  following command fills all area I/O row clusters on ESD,
                shoulder, and gap sites with a filler cell  A0_123  with  pre-
                placed status:

                addAIoFiller -cell AO_123 -setPreplaced

              * The  following  command  adds area I/O filler cells,IOFILL and
                IOFILL_HALF,to fill all the gaps in all area I/O row clusters:

                addAIoFiller -allAIORowCluster  -onlyGap  -cellList  {  IOFILL
                IOFILL_HALF }

